{"parse":{"title":"Save Beirut Heritage","pageid":36475508,"revid":855587463,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Save Beirut Heritage</b> (also known as <b>Save Beirut's Heritage</b>) is a cultural heritage organization based in <a href=\"/wiki/Beirut\" title=\"Beirut\">Beirut</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Lebanon\" title=\"Lebanon\">Lebanon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NYT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The organization was founded in 2010 with the aims to preserve architectural heritage within Beirut, which has come under increased threat of destruction through rampant <a href=\"/wiki/Urbanization\" title=\"Urbanization\">urbanization</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The organization started as a group on <a href=\"/wiki/Facebook\" title=\"Facebook\">Facebook</a>, highlighting and vocalising the dangers facing Beirut's ancient sites and traditional buildings. The group now has over eight thousand members and operates a twenty-four-hour <a href=\"/wiki/Hotline\" title=\"Hotline\">hotline</a> for the city's residents to call if they fear a building may be in danger from demolition or construction activities.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NYT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The organization has organized several <a href=\"/wiki/Petition\" title=\"Petition\">petitions</a> and assisted with <a href=\"/wiki/Demonstration_(people)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Demonstration (people)\">public demonstrations</a> to protest and protect historic buildings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Their efforts have resulted in the <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Culture_(Lebanon)\" title=\"Ministry of Culture (Lebanon)\">Ministry of Culture</a> issuing a halt order on their demolition. The organization encourages people in the city to monitor properties for illegal demolition and highlights the different ploys used by developers to try and tear down these buildings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NYT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Interviewed by the <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Times\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York Times\">New York Times</a>, the organization's spokesman, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Giorgio_Tarraf&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Giorgio Tarraf (page does not exist)\">Giorgio Tarraf</a> said <i>\u201cThese old buildings are not only pretty, they are financially viable, tourists want to come and see our old city, they don\u2019t want to see towers. They can see towers anywhere.\u201d</i> He also spoke of a survey conducted by the government in the 1990s that cataloged more than one thousand historic buildings in Beirut. <i>\u201cToday we estimate the number of remaining traditional buildings to be less than 300, so you can see how dramatic the demolition is, how fast our old city is being transformed.\u201d</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NYT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Speaking to the <a href=\"/wiki/Associated_Press\" title=\"Associated Press\">Associated Press</a>, activist and spokesman <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Naji_Raji&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Naji Raji (page does not exist)\">Naji Raji</a> said: <i>\u201cModernization should not be at the expense of history.\u201d</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Save_Beirut_Heritage&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-NYT-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-NYT_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-NYT_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-NYT_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-NYT_1-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/27/arts/27iht-m27cbeirut.html?pagewanted=all\">Wood, Josh., Beirut's Old Buildings Again Under Threat, The New York Times, January 26, 2011</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Sfeir, Mia., Femme Magazine - Pr\u00e9histoire VS Urbanisation, le t\u00e9moignage d\u2019Henri Fleisch - Issue 206 - P.70 Published June 1, 2010</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thenational.ae/news/world/middle-east/developers-threaten-beiruts-architectural-heritage\">Collard, Rebecca., Developers threaten Beirut's architectural heritage, The National, 16 September, 2011.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Karam, Zeina. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://bigstory.ap.org/article/construction-frenzy-beirut-alters-city-skyline\">\"Construction Frenzy Beirut Alters City Skyline\"</a>. <i>Associated Press</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Associated+Press&amp;rft.atitle=Construction+Frenzy+Beirut+Alters+City+Skyline&amp;rft.aulast=Karam&amp;rft.aufirst=Zeina&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbigstory.